programme.desc: A profile of the former boxer, a four-time world super-middleweight champion considered among the elite performers in his weight class. After rising through the domestic ranks and winning both the British and Commonwealth titles, Froch claimed his first world crown by defeating Jean Pascal in 2008, and was a dominant fighter on the world scene from that point on. His legacy was assured in May 2014 when he defeated fellow Brit George Groves in a rematch at Wembley Stadium in what proved to be his final fight. That contest drew what was then the largest attendance for a boxing bout in the UK since the Second World War at 80,000

programme.title: NFL Playoff: Jacksonville Jaguars at Pittsburgh Steelers
programme.desc: Jacksonville Jaguars (11-6) at Pittsburgh Steelers (13-3) in an AFC Divisional game. From Heinz Field. The upstart Jaguars won 30-9 here on Oct. 8, returning two of their 5 INTs of Ben Roethlisberger for TDs, while Leonard Fournette ran for 181 yards. Seven of Pittsburgh's eight Pro Bowl players are on offense, while the Jags have four on defense. The Steelers have eight playoff wins since a divisional-round loss here to Jacksonville 10 years ago in Mike Tomlin's postseason debut. (cc)

programme.title: NFL Playoff: New Orleans Saints at Minnesota Vikings
programme.sub-title: New Orleans Saints at Minnesota Vikings
programme.desc: New Orleans Saints (12-5) at Minnesota Vikings (13-3) in an NFC Divisional game. From U.S. Bank Stadium. Mike Zimmer's Vikings opened 2017 with a 29-19 win over New Orleans, keeping QB Drew Brees and Co. out of the end zone until the last two minutes. Everson Griffen and Xavier Rhodes head Minnesota's defense, while the Saints boast a Pro Bowl RB tandem in Alvin Kamara and Mark Ingram. The Vikes' last playoff win was eight years ago, followed by an NFC title-game loss to the Saints. (cc)
